# ShowTracker

Cross-platform show/anime/movie tracking app built with Expo (React Native + Web), Convex backend, NativeWind styling.

## Tech Stack
- Expo SDK 52+ (React Native + React Native Web)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Expo Router v4 (file-based routing)
- NativeWind v4 (Tailwind CSS for RN)
- Convex (real-time DB, server functions, auth)
- Zustand + react-native-mmkv (client state)
- APIs: TMDB, TVMaze, AniList, Jikan

## Project Structure
- `app/` — Expo Router screens and layouts
- `components/` — Reusable UI components
- `lib/` — Business logic, API clients, utilities
- `lib/api/` — External API clients
- `convex/` — Convex backend (schema, queries, mutations, actions)
- `constants/` — Theme colors, config values
- `hooks/` — Custom React hooks
- `store/` — Zustand stores
- `types/` — Shared TypeScript types

## Code Conventions
- Functional components only, prefer named exports
- Use NativeWind className for all styling (no StyleSheet.create)
- Convex: one file per domain (shows.ts, users.ts, lists.ts)
- API clients return normalized types from lib/api/types.ts
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- Imports: absolute paths via `@/` alias

## Git Workflow
- Never commit unless the user explicitly asks — do not auto-commit
- Never push directly to main — always create a branch + PR
- Branch naming: feat/, fix/, docs/ prefixes
- All PRs reviewed by CodeRabbit before merge

## Never Do
- Never commit API keys or secrets
- Never make API calls directly from components — use lib/api/ clients
- Never store images in Convex — use URL references
- Never bypass Convex for data that needs to sync
- Never use StyleSheet.create — use NativeWind className
- Never push directly to main

## Key Commands
- `npx expo start` — Dev server
- `npx convex dev` — Convex dev backend
- `npx expo lint` — Lint

